      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "SAVED LISTS PANEL"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "This function displays a select list of saved lists.  In practical"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "terms a saved list is a select list that you have decided to save"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "under a symbolic name."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "A typical application of saved lists is to keep track and act upon"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "groups of related files. For example a programmer might be working"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "on ten related source files out of a larger set. By creating and"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "then saving a list of these files, he can repeatedly access them"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "without regard to the larger file set. When the activity related to"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "a particular list is complete, the list is deleted.  One simple way"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "to think about saved lists is as micro-projects."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Use the SAVELIST primary command to save a list."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
